23/03/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The EU envoy for the Montenegrin independence referendum, Miroslav Lajcak, urged Belgrade and Podgorica on Wednesday (22 March) to start discussing relations after the independence poll. 
Lajcak said citizens of Montenegro have the right to know what they can expect after the 21 May referendum.
Also Wednesday, China donated military equipment worth around 517,500 euros to the Serbia-Montenegro Army. 
At a ceremony in Belgrade, officials said co-operation in the military sector would intensify in the future. 
(Tanjug, Mina, Xinhua - 22/03/06)
